<p>Most businesses treat SEO and brand building as separate efforts. One team writes blog posts for keywords. Another team runs brand campaigns. The two never talk.</p>
<p>That disconnect costs you rankings. Google now uses brand signals as a ranking factor. Nearly <a href="https://ahrefs.com/blog/almost-half-of-google-searches-are-branded-study/">50% of all Google searches are branded</a>, and businesses that ignore their brand presence in search lose clicks to competitors, review sites, and AI-generated summaries.</p>
<p>A brand SEO strategy fixes this. It aligns your brand identity with your search visibility so Google treats your business as a trusted entity, not just another domain.</p>
<p>We publish 3,500+ blog posts across 70+ industries. We see the same pattern every time: businesses with strong brand signals rank faster and hold positions longer than those relying on keywords alone.</p>
