<h2>What Is a Brand SEO Strategy?</h2>
<p>A brand SEO strategy is the process of optimizing your entire online presence around your brand identity. It goes beyond targeting keywords. It ensures that when someone searches for your company name, your product, or topics you own, Google returns results you control.</p>
<p>Traditional SEO focuses on ranking for non-branded terms. Brand SEO focuses on how your brand appears across all search results, including branded queries, Knowledge Panels, People Also Ask boxes, and AI-generated overviews.</p>
<h3>Brand SEO vs. Traditional SEO</h3>
<p>Traditional SEO targets informational and transactional keywords. You pick a keyword, write a page, build links, and try to rank. Brand SEO takes a wider approach.</p>
