<p>The mistake most businesses make: they focus entirely on non-branded keywords and ignore their <a href="/blog/brand-entity-seo/">branded search presence</a>. When a prospect finally searches your name, they find outdated listings, competitor ads, or third-party review sites instead of your own content.</p>
<h3>The Click-Through Rate Advantage</h3>
<p><a href="https://backlinko.com/google-ctr-stats">Backlinko's CTR study</a> shows that the number 1 organic result gets 27.6% of all clicks. For branded searches, that number jumps even higher because users are looking specifically for you.</p>
<p>Higher click-through rates send positive engagement signals to Google. When users consistently click your result over others for branded queries, it reinforces your authority. This positive feedback loop benefits your non-branded rankings too.</p>
<h3>Branded Search as a Ranking Signal</h3>
<p>Google has never confirmed that branded search volume is a direct ranking factor. But the correlation is undeniable.</p>
<p>Businesses that invest in brand awareness see improvements across their entire keyword portfolio. The mechanism works like this: more brand searches lead to more clicks, which leads to better engagement metrics, which leads to higher rankings for related non-branded terms.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="Brand SEO strategy authority statistics including branded search volume and conversion rates" src="/images/blog/brand-seo-authority-stats.webp" /></p>
<p>Think of branded search as a trust signal. A company nobody searches for has no proven demand. A company that generates thousands of branded searches per month has proven market relevance. Google factors this into its assessment of <a href="/blog/domain-authority-guide/">domain authority</a> and trustworthiness.</p>
