<h3>Monitor Share of Search</h3>
<p>Share of search measures your brand's search volume relative to competitors. It is one of the best predictors of market share.</p>
<p>Calculate it by dividing your branded search volume by the total branded search volume for all competitors in your category. Track this in your <a href="/blog/seo-reporting-guide/">SEO reporting</a> dashboard.</p>
<p>A rising share of search means you are capturing more mind share in your market. A declining share means competitors are growing faster.</p>
<h3>Brand Mentions in AI Search</h3>
<p>AI search platforms now account for a growing share of discovery. Track how your brand appears in <a href="/blog/ai-overview-optimization/">AI Overviews</a>, ChatGPT responses, and Perplexity answers.</p>
<p>Monitor your <a href="/blog/ai-share-of-voice/">AI share of voice</a> by regularly querying AI platforms with your target topics. Document when your brand gets cited, what context it appears in, and how the citation changes over time.</p>
<p>Tools like Profound, Otterly, and Peec AI track AI citations automatically. Add AI visibility tracking to your brand SEO measurement stack alongside traditional <a href="/blog/seo-statistics/">SEO metrics</a>.</p>
